args: On the morning of Dragonyule, Cleo and Notte\nfind themselves once again struggling to\ncreate the perfect cake.
So how are we changing up the cake\nthis time, Cleo?
You wanted to make one that all of us\ncan enjoy together, right?
Yes. I intend to customize the cake to\neach person's specific tastes.
Which means everyone will love it!
Hey, wait. Can you even DO that?
Who do you think you're talking to?
I single-handedly manage essentially all\ncuisine-related affairs at the Halidom!
So you know what everyone likes!
There's no time left to dawdle before the\nDragonyule party. Let's get to baking.
I'm going to stir the batter, so would you\nbe so kind as to pour in some milk?
Heeeere we go! *glug* Is this right?
Uh, Cleo? Are you stirring more than\nyou did before?
Good eye, Notte. This is because Elisanne\nenjoys a soft, fluffy cake.
And to make the batter nice and fluffy,\nyou have to mix it quite vigorously.
No kidding? I never knew that!
Now then, would you pour the sugar into\nthat bowl of cream there?
No, stop! That's far too much!
Huuuh? But that's how much we put in\nlast time.
I forgot to mention this, but I'd like to\nkeep the sugar to a moderate amount.
Ranzal doesn't have much of a palate for\noverly sweet things.
Heh. You WOULD know that, Cleo.\nNo detail gets past you!
And now to arrange some berries on top...
Oh man, berries are the best.
I know you think as much, so I grabbed\nsome extras while I was in town.
I love it! Let's get 'em on there!
Distribute them however you wish—\nbut don't steal any!
Hee hee! Can't get anything past you.
All right. That should be everything.
Everyone is gonna fall all over themselves\ntrying to get a piece; we may need to\nmake 'em take numbers or something.
I have a strange sensation that the cake\nis still...missing something.
For reals? But it looks so tasty...
I'm confident in the flavor, of course,\nand am certain everyone will quite like it.
And yet, I just can't shake the feeling that\nas a cake for everyone to enjoy together,\nit is somehow lacking.
Maybe you need to add something that\nshows how much love and care you put\ninto this whole project?
Ah! I have it! One moment, please.
If I just put this on top... Yes!\nNOW it's finished.
Aw! You made little sugar cookies—\nand they look like US!
They do indeed. I made one for everyone\nhere in the castle.
I think this will ensure that everyone\ntruly enjoys the cake.
Although it's a bit of a rush job,\nso I fear they're not exact likenesses.
You shut your mouth, Cleo.\nThese are ADORBS.
Just looking at 'em makes it clear how\nmuch love you put into this!
In that case, I will consider my work done.
Let us take it to the party at once.
